---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const structuredData = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Organization",
  "name": "ToolCalcs",
  "url": "https://toolcalcs.com",
  "description": "Free, accurate online calculators for finance, health, math, and everyday needs.",
  "foundingDate": "2024",
  "sameAs": [],
  "contactPoint": {
    "@type": "ContactPoint",
    "email": "contact@toolcalcs.com",
    "contactType": "customer support"
  }
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About ToolCalcs - Free Online Calculator Tools"
  description="ToolCalcs provides free, accurate, and easy-to-use online calculators for finance, health, and everyday math. Learn about our mission, tools, and editorial process."
  structuredData={structuredData}
>
  <div class="page-content">
    <h1>About ToolCalcs</h1>

    <p>ToolCalcs is a free online resource providing accurate, easy-to-use calculators and tools for everyday needs. Whether you are planning your finances, tracking health goals, solving math problems, or converting units, our tools are designed to give you quick, reliable results with clear explanations.</p>

    <h2>Our Story</h2>
    <p>ToolCalcs started in 2024 with a simple idea: the best online calculators should be free, fast, and transparent. Too many calculator sites hide behind paywalls, require sign-ups, or run calculations on remote servers without showing their work. We wanted to build something different.</p>
    <p>Every tool on ToolCalcs runs entirely in your browser. We show the formulas, explain the math, and let you verify every result. No accounts, no hidden fees, no data collection. Just the answers you need, as fast as possible.</p>

    <h2>Meet the Team</h2>
    <div class="team-card">
      <div class="team-info">
        <h3>Editorial Team</h3>
        <p>Our content team combines expertise in mathematics, finance, health sciences, and web development. Every calculator is built by developers with domain expertise, and every educational article is reviewed for accuracy before publication.</p>
        <p>We follow a rigorous editorial process: research authoritative sources, implement standard formulas, cross-validate results, and provide transparent step-by-step explanations. Our financial calculators reference IRS tax brackets and standard amortization equations. Our health tools use clinically recognized formulas like Mifflin-St Jeor for TDEE and WHO-recommended BMI calculations.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>What We Offer</h2>
    <p>ToolCalcs has grown into a comprehensive platform with <strong>113 interactive calculators</strong> across 8 categories, <strong>38 tests and games</strong>, <strong>25 web tools</strong>, <strong>57 printable worksheets</strong>, <strong>100+ educational blog articles</strong>, and thousands of quick-reference pages.</p>

    <h3>Interactive Calculators</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong><a href="/financial-calculators/">Financial Calculators (34):</a></strong> Mortgage, compound interest, loan amortization, take-home pay, retirement savings, auto loan, 401(k), investment, ROI, credit card payoff, debt-to-income, net worth, house affordability, rent vs buy, profit margin, student loan, refinance, FIRE, and more.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/health-calculators/">Health Calculators (15):</a></strong> BMI, BMR, TDEE, calorie, body fat, ideal weight, pregnancy due date, pace, ovulation, macro, sleep, water intake, pregnancy weight gain, protein, and BAC calculators.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/math-calculators/">Math Calculators (16):</a></strong> Percentage, percentage change, fraction, GPA, random number, standard deviation, area, probability, average, triangle, LCM/GCF, prime checker, quadratic formula, and volume tools.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/date-time-calculators/">Date & Time Calculators (9):</a></strong> Age calculator, date difference, days-until countdown, time zone converter, business days, time duration, timestamp, hours calculator, and day-of-week calculators.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/conversion-calculators/">Conversion Calculators (8):</a></strong> Unit converter, currency converter, temperature, data size, length, weight, speed, and cooking measurement converters.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/everyday-calculators/">Everyday Calculators (13):</a></strong> Tip, discount, hours, square footage, gas cost, electricity cost, word counter, sales tax, grade, fuel economy, age difference, and more.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/construction-calculators/">Construction Calculators (12):</a></strong> Concrete, flooring, paint, roofing, fence, mulch, drywall, deck, solar panel, gravel, tile, and stair calculators.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/astrology-calculators/">Astrology Calculators (6):</a></strong> Zodiac sign, zodiac compatibility, Chinese zodiac, numerology, angel number, and tarot reading tools.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Tests, Games, Tools & Worksheets</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong><a href="/test/">Tests & Games (38):</a></strong> IQ test, personality tests (DISC, Dark Triad), mental health screenings (GAD-7, PHQ-9), cognitive tests (reaction time, memory, typing speed), brain games (chimp test, Stroop effect), and more.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/tools/">Web Tools (25):</a></strong> JSON formatter, password generator, QR code generator, color converter, image compressor, regex tester, hash generator, and other developer and everyday tools.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/worksheets/">Worksheets (57):</a></strong> Printable math worksheets for Pre-K through 10th grade, plus reading comprehension worksheets. Generate unlimited problems, print, and practice.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/blog/">Educational Blog (100+):</a></strong> In-depth guides covering finance, health, psychology, technology, science, and everyday math topics.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How We Build Our Tools</h2>
    <p>Every calculator and tool on ToolCalcs goes through a careful development process:</p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Research:</strong> We study industry-standard formulas from authoritative sources, including government agencies (IRS, BLS), academic references, and professional organizations.</li>
      <li><strong>Implementation:</strong> Calculations are coded using precise mathematical formulas. Financial calculators use standard amortization equations; health calculators use clinically recognized formulas like the Mifflin-St Jeor equation for TDEE and the WHO-recommended BMI formula.</li>
      <li><strong>Validation:</strong> Results are cross-checked against multiple trusted sources and reference implementations to verify accuracy.</li>
      <li><strong>Transparency:</strong> Where possible, we display the formulas and calculation steps directly on the page so users can verify our work.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Why Trust ToolCalcs?</h2>
    <ul class="trust-list">
      <li><strong>Client-side calculations:</strong> All computations run directly in your browser. Your data never leaves your device, and nothing is sent to any server.</li>
      <li><strong>Open formulas:</strong> We show the mathematical formulas and step-by-step breakdowns so you can understand and verify every result.</li>
      <li><strong>No account required:</strong> Use any tool instantly, without sign-ups, logins, or personal information.</li>
      <li><strong>Regular updates:</strong> We continuously review our tools for accuracy, add new features, and fix issues reported by our users.</li>
      <li><strong>Free and accessible:</strong> Every tool is free to use with no paywalls or premium tiers.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Accuracy & Privacy</h2>
    <p>All calculations are performed directly in your browser using JavaScript. We do not send your input data to any server. Your numbers stay on your device.</p>
    <p>Our calculators are for informational and educational purposes only. They should not replace professional financial, medical, or legal advice. For important decisions, always consult a qualified professional.</p>
    <p>For full details on how we handle your data, please see our <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a> and <a href="/terms-of-service/">Terms of Service</a>.</p>

    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
    <p>Have a question, suggestion, or found a bug? We would love to hear from you. Visit our <a href="/contact/">contact page</a> or email us at <a href="mailto:contact@toolcalcs.com">contact@toolcalcs.com</a>.</p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-content { max-width: 700px; line-height: 1.8; }
  h1 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  h2 { font-size: 1.3rem; margin: 28px 0 12px; }
  h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; margin: 20px 0 10px; }
  p { margin-bottom: 12px; }
  ul, ol { margin: 0 0 16px 24px; }
  li { margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .trust-list li { margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .team-card {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 24px;
    margin: 16px 0;
  }
  .team-info h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }
  .team-info p {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
</style>
